Many of these women justify their antichoice beliefs by simply pointing to the large numbers of

They perceive HIV as mostly a foreign and elitist disease, and therefore no one’s responsibility but the

Given the restrictions on access to abortion services in Namibia, the Ark foundation, out of its compassion, is buying, distributing and educating about condoms as well as mobilizing women all along the promotional cycle of these bloody drugs through responsible parenting and responsible sex. The Ark Foundation is also assisting women to access the sexual and reproductive health rights and HIV/AIDS that they are legally assured by the government of Namibia as contained in the Constitution of Namibia and the act of the elected government of Namibia in 1993 from the time of Namibia’s liberation.
The Ark Foundation has therefore taken it up to fight diligently against a harm culture in Namibia through prevention of STIs and unwanted pregnancies (including less frequent abortion cases). With an average yearly income of $150.00 per family, abortion is not something that can be readily agreed in the formation of a decision because of the unaffordable healthcare bills. This is why education is one of the infrastructures of prevention of abortion. The Arks Foundation does also provide nominal compensation of $350.00 for an every pretty-mature woman
